# SpecStoryTDD

> **Hybrid TDD/SDD Framework** — Align User Stories with OpenAPI Specifications, detect conflicts automatically, and generate Pytest test suites with AI.

[![Python 3.11+](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.11%2B-blue.svg)](https://www.python.org/downloads/)
[![FastAPI](https://img.shields.io/badge/FastAPI-0.111%2B-009688.svg)](https://fastapi.tiangolo.com)
[![LangChain](https://img.shields.io/badge/LangChain-0.2%2B-1C3C3C.svg)](https://python.langchain.com)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](LICENSE)

---

## 📖 What is SpecStoryTDD?

SpecStoryTDD bridges the gap between **product requirements** and **API contracts**. It takes:

- A **User Story** (Markdown) describing the expected behaviour from a user's perspective, and  
- An **OpenAPI 3.x Specification** (JSON) describing the technical contract of the API.

…and automatically:

1. **Detects logical conflicts** — e.g. a story expects HTTP 401 but the spec only defines 400; or a field that must be hidden is present in the response schema.
2. **Generates a Pytest test suite** — ready-to-run tests that encode the acceptance criteria and expose the conflicts.

This approach combines **Specification-Driven Development (SDD)** and **Test-Driven Development (TDD)** into a single AI-powered feedback loop.

